The paper deals with a classic problem in the data stream literature, specifically the estimation of frequency moments of an underlying vector presented as a sequence of additive updates in a stream. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also proposes a new algorithm that achieves better space bounds in the random-order model of insertion-only streams, which involves randomness and probability, making it relevant to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the optimality of the proposed algorithm, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
